modules.description: Processes HTMX requests by handling swap, target, and trigger attributes. Works with HTTP requests, response bodies, and HTML fragments. Enables dynamic page updates without full reloads, such as replacing a section of a page or triggering client-side animations.

Provides functions to inspect and manipulate Htmx request attributes such as triggers, targets, and prompts, and to control client-side navigation and event triggering. Works with Dream.request and Dream.response types to extract information from Htmx requests and construct responses with URL updates or event triggers. Used to handle dynamic page updates, form submissions, and client-side interactions without full page reloads.
